  "titleEn": "That (Masculine)",
  "description": "Learn to identify distant objects using the demonstrative pronoun ذَلِكَ (that) with masculine nouns.",
  "vocabulary": ["word-010", "word-011", "word-012", "word-013", "word-014"],
  "grammarPoints": ["gp-003"],
  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "The Far Demonstrative ذَلِكَ",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الإشارة للبعيد",
      "content": [
        "This lesson introduces ذَلِكَ (that) for masculine nouns referring to distant objects. It is pronounced 'dhālika' but written without the alif after ذ.",
        "The conjunction وَ (and) is used to connect words and sentences. It is always written attached to the following word."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "ذَلِكَ is used for masculine singular nouns that are far (that)",
        "The conjunction وَ is written attached to the next word, not separate",
        "هَذَا is for near objects, ذَلِكَ is for far objects"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "هَذَا بَيْتٌ وَذَلِكَ مَسْجِدٌ", "english": "This is a house and that is a mosque" },
        { "arabic": "ذَلِكَ نَجْمٌ", "english": "That is a star" },
        { "arabic": "ذَلِكَ جَبَلٌ", "english": "That is a mountain" }
      ]
    }
  ],
